   "source": [
    "# Model Geometry (Pyvista)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "At any point during model creation, you can run the :func:`opstool.vis.pyvista.plot_model` function to visualize the current model's geometric details. \n",
    "This function operates based on post-processed data saved during the modeling process, ensuring accurate visualization.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can use :func:`opstool.vis.pyvista.plot_model` anywhere within your model script. \n",
    "It reads the predefined data, such as nodes and elements, and generates a visual representation of the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import opstool as opst\n",
    "import opstool.vis.pyvista as opsvis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, we use a built-in example from ``opstool``, which is an example of a cable-stayed bridge model primarily composed of frame elements and shell elements.\n",
    "For your own model script, simply place the :func:`opstool.vis.plotly.plot_model` function anywhere you need visualization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## A Bridge Example"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "opst.load_ops_examples(\"CableStayedBridge\")\n",
    "# or your model code here"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "quick plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plotter = opsvis.plot_model()\n",
    "plotter.show()\n",
    "# plotter.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Saving Model Data (Optional)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "We can first save the model geometry data by assigning a unique label to the result database using the parameter\n",
    "**`odb_tag`**. \n",
    "This label is used to identify the data. \n",
    "For more details, see :func:`opstool.post.save_model_data`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  Model data has been saved to <span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">.opstool.output/ModelData-</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">nc</span>!\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Model data has been saved to \u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m.opstool.output/ModelData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30mnc\u001b[0m!\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "opst.post.save_model_data(odb_tag=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "### Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "We use the :func:`opstool.vis.pyvista.set_plot_props` function to predefine some common visualization properties, which will affect all subsequent visualizations of models, eigenvalues, and responses."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "opsvis.set_plot_props(point_size=0, line_width=3, notebook=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    ".. Note::\n",
    "    If you are not working in Jupyter Notebook or JupyterLab, ensure that **`notebook=False`**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Visualization is straightforward; simply call the :func:`opstool.vis.pyvista.plot_model` function. \n",
    "The **odb_tag** parameter helps you identify which dataset to use. \n",
    "For details on various parameters, refer to the :func:`opstool.vis.pvista.plot_model`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  Loading model data from <span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">.opstool.output/ModelData-</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">nc</span> <span style=\"color: #808000; text-decoration-color: #808000\">...</span>\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Loading model data from \u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m.opstool.output/ModelData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30mnc\u001b[0m \u001b[33m...\u001b[0m\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",

       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"

     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter = opsvis.plot_model(odb_tag=1)\n",
    "plotter.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")\n",
    "# plotter.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "The function :func:`opstool.vis.pyvista.plot_model` returns a `pyvista.Plotter <https://docs.pyvista.org/api/plotting/_autosummary/pyvista.plotter>`_. object, which you can visualize using the `show` method.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can use\n",
    "`Plotter.show <https://docs.pyvista.org/api/plotting/_autosummary/pyvista.plotter.show#pyvista.Plotter.show>`_.\n",
    "to display the plotting window.\n",
    "\n",
    "You can also use\n",
    "`Plotter.export_html <https://docs.pyvista.org/api/plotting/_autosummary/pyvista.plotter.export_html#pyvista.Plotter.export_html>`_.\n",
    "to export this plotter as an interactive scene to an HTML file."
   ]
  }
